snippet.textDisplay:
10:05 The AF is the "problem" of these type of sensor starting from quad or nona-bayer for this S20 Ultra. The AF accuracy that you expect is of dual-pixel AF which none of these Samsung sensors have touting quad and nona-bayer arrangement. As far as sensor development is concerned on these types of sensors, only Sony were the ones that actively solving the issue with their 2x2 OCL on IMX686, a quad-bayer 64MP 1/1.7" sensor.


The focus bounce is what were expected based on the HMX/HM1's current specifications. Is this a problem? I would say NO, if you know the specs the sensors have. But if the user is blindly buying a product and expecting "greatness" with the justification that it is a flagship then they would consider this as problem. The AF is what I would say "fine", just don't put it beside or even compare it with any phone with dual-pixel AF.
